P(C=T|X=T,D=T) = ?

P(C=T|do X=T, D=T) IS NOT THE SAME THING

P(X|Y)= P(X,Y)/P(Y)
P(X,Y)=P(X|Y)P(Y)
P(X,Y)=P(Y|X)P(Y)

P(C=T|X=T, D=T)
...    =F,  =T
...    =T,  =F

ordering:  S, P, C, X, D

\aside{

P(S, P, C) = P(S)*P(P|S)*P(C|S,P)
           = P(S)*P(P)*P(C|S,P)
           = 0.1 * 0.3 * 0.05 = 0.0015

}

