two photons can occupy the same area in space.  electrons can absorb photons.  electrons are tiny.  photons are massive.  they can be absorbed by the electrons.  this increases the electron.  photons are a wave of possibilities that propagates through space.  it is a transvrese wave.  sound is a compression wave.  the sine wave has a plane of polarization.  normal light has all kinds of directions of planes.

if the photon makes it through a polarization filter, it depends on the plane of polarization.  if it makes it through, it will now be polarized to that plain of polarization.  if you ahve a second filter identical to the first, 100% get through.  if you put it at 90 degrees to the polarization, the probability to get through is 0.

if you take three filters, one horizontal, one 45 degrees and one 90 degrees, then 1/8th of the photon getting through.  a 45 degree would be 50%.  and the first one is 50%.  so all three is .5 * .5 * .5 = 1/8.

